# Vendored (adapted) from
# https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/path/path.n3
# Adaptation: dropped the leading "[] log:table :path." tabling hint (a pure
# performance directive using the "[...]" anonymous blank-node-property-list
# shorthand, which this crate's grammar does not target -- see n3_parser.rs's
# test_parse_blank_nodes). It has no effect on which facts are entailed.
#
# EYE's own query for this case is the ground pattern "{ :b :path :b } => { :b
# :path :b }", i.e. "does this one specific fact hold", so EYE's answer file
# (reasoning/path/path-answer.n3) is only a *subset* of the full closure
# materialize() computes (the :path relation here is the full symmetric-
# transitive closure of the :road graph, i.e. many more pairs than just
# `:b :path :b`) -- the expected file below asserts that one EYE-verified fact
# as a subset check, consistent with how this runner compares results.
@prefix : <urn:example:>.

:a :road :b.
:a :road :c.
:b :road :d.
:c :road :d.

{ ?X :path ?Y } <= { ?X :path ?Z. ?Z :path ?Y }.
{ ?X :path ?Y } <= { ?X :road ?Y }.
{ ?X :path ?Y } <= { ?Y :road ?X }.
